It is strange that you mention Josephus, since Wells claims 
that historians and theologians widely regard the two mentions in Josephus to be 
Christian interpolations. I have also heard others make this claim.

In addition, Wells claims that there are areas of dis-harmony in the four 
gospel accounts. Any harmony that you find is perhaps not surprising, as there 
seems to be evidence that Matthew and Luke are based on Mark and other
documents.

